mmand(s)."]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.versions_from_parentdir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "parentdir_prefix", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "root", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Try to determine the version from the parent directory name.\n\nSource tarballs conventionally unpack into a directory that includes both\nthe project name and a version string. We will also support searching up\ntwo directory levels for an appropriately named parent directory"]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.git_get_keywords", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "versionfile_abs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Extract version information from the given file."]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.git_versions_from_keywords", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "keywords", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "tag_prefix", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get version information from git keywords."]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.git_pieces_from_vcs", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "tag_prefix", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "root", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "run_command", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get version from 'git describe' in the root of the source tree.\n\nThis only gets called if the git-archive 'subst' keywords were *not*\nexpanded, and _version.py hasn't already been rewritten with a short\nversion string, meaning we're inside a checked out source tree."]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.plus_or_dot", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pieces", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return a + if we don't already have one, else return a ."]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.render_pep440", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pieces", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Build up version string, with post-release \"local version identifier\".\n\nOur goal: TAG[+DISTANCE.gHEX[.dirty]] . Note that if you\nget a tagged build and then dirty it, you'll get TAG+0.gHEX.dirty\n\nExceptions:\n1: no tags. git_describe was just HEX. 0+untagged.DISTANCE.gHEX[.dirty]"]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.render_pep440_pre", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pieces", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["TAG[.post.devDISTANCE] -- No -dirty.\n\nExceptions:\n1: no tags. 0.post.devDISTANCE"]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.render_pep440_post", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pieces", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["TAG[.postDISTANCE[.dev0]+gHEX] .\n\nThe \".dev0\" means dirty. Note that .dev0 sorts backwards\n(a dirty tree will appear \"older\" than the corresponding clean one),\nbut you shouldn't be releasing software with -dirty anyways.\n\nExceptions:\n1: no tags. 0.postDISTANCE[.dev0]"]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.render_pep440_old", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pieces", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["TAG[.postDISTANCE[.dev0]] .\n\nThe \".dev0\" means dirty.\n\nEexceptions:\n1: no tags. 0.postDISTANCE[.dev0]"]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.render_git_describe", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pieces", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["TAG[-DISTANCE-gHEX][-dirty].\n\nLike 'git describe --tags --dirty --always'.\n\nExceptions:\n1: no tags. HEX[-dirty]  (note: no 'g' prefix)"]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.render_git_describe_long", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pieces", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["TAG-DISTANCE-gHEX[-dirty].\n\nLike 'git describe --tags --dirty --always -long'.\nThe distance/hash is unconditional.\n\nExceptions:\n1: no tags. HEX[-dirty]  (note: no 'g' prefix)"]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.render", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "pieces", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "style", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Render the given version pieces into the requested style."]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.get_versions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get version information or return default if unable to do so."]}], "variables": [{"name": "qt6_tools._version.LONG_VERSION_PY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.HANDLERS", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "qt6_tools._version.VersioneerConfig", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Container for Versioneer configuration parameters."]}, {"name": "qt6_tools._version.NotThisMethod", "bases": ["Exception"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Exception raised if a method is not valid for the current scenario."]}], "exports": []}]}